h2 - Uploading a Video
p - Adding Content to My Media • Resource • BYU-Idaho Learning and Teaching (byui.edu)
h2 - Help us Find Your Video (Metadata)
p - Accessibility Services can help support your efforts to provide captioned videos. To help us make sure we can find your videos when needed, please help us by completing the metadata fields for your uploaded videos.
h3 - Tags
p - Add a tag to the video that includes your course code and number (ex. MATH 304)
p - Add a tag to the video that includes the week number the video is used in your course (ex. W02)
p - If the video is not for a course, add a tag with the location, office, or event.
h3 - Hearing Impaired
p - Choose “Yes” if you have received a captioning accommodation request
p - Choose “No” for all other reasons
h3 - Video Purpose
p - One or Two Semesters: select this option if your video is only for a limited time. Examples include things like office hours, Zoom meetings, or other videos you do not plan to use again.
p - Long running course: select this option if you will be using the content for longer than two semesters.
p - Master Course for Online Learning: select this option if the video appears is a master course (campus or online) that will be used in multiple sections for the foreseeable future.
p - Campus wide broadcast/communication/website: select this option if the video will be posted publicly on a BYU-Idaho website, social media, YouTube, or other platform. Anything that has a publishing status of public will use this option unless in a course.
p - None of the above: select this option if none of the others fit your video use. This option should also be used by students submitting videos for assignments.
h3 - Publishing Status
p - Unlisted will make the video available only through the link; it will not be available through a search on video.byui.edu. This is the recommended publishing status for most course videos.
p - You may need to access My Media through video.byui.edu to use the Unlisted status.
p - Published will be used for videos made public on video.byui.edu. These can be found through the search feature.
p - Private videos are only viewable by you or co-editors/owners/publishers. Other users will not be able to view, even if they have a link.
